cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG

This paper deals with game theory and coordination games, which are typically studied in the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of graphs and networks in the game also suggests a possible fit in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The study of equilibria and optimization in the game may also make it relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. Finally, the use of bounds and complexity analysis may also make it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
